Crime victims seeking emergency help are waiting up to 50 per cent longer for assistance compared with three years ago with response times increasing by an extra couple of minutes
Analysis of Home Office figures show that in areas such as Bedfordshire as well as Devon and Cornwall
response times are now at least 50 per cent longer than they were three years ago
Crime victims in Cambridgeshire and South Wales wait on average 14 minutes
